snippet.textDisplay: It’s been four years since the release of Shelter but four years felt like nothing. I had been listening to the Worlds album obsessively like two years ago. I remember it being the senior year of high school and being so overwhelmed by social anxiety that I’d hide in the bathroom before school started and during lunch and I would just stand in a stall and blast that album through my headphones and draw on the walls. Those songs—Divinity, Hear The Bells, Years of War, Lionhearted, all of the songs—gave me solace from the war going on in my mind. I’m so happy and so grateful for more music and that more music is coming! More solace is on its way, more liberation of the soul
snippet.textOriginal: It’s been four years since the release of Shelter but four years felt like nothing. I had been listening to the Worlds album obsessively like two years ago. I remember it being the senior year of high school and being so overwhelmed by social anxiety that I’d hide in the bathroom before school started and during lunch and I would just stand in a stall and blast that album through my headphones and draw on the walls. Those songs—Divinity, Hear The Bells, Years of War, Lionhearted, all of the songs—gave me solace from the war going on in my mind.
